Nat, Nat, did you
hear that?

27:20.013 --> 27:22.307
What? it! I did it!

27:22.390 --> 27:22.891
Oh, that's
great.

27:22.974 --> 27:24.851
Steve, Steve, sit down.

27:24.934 --> 27:25.769
{\an1}Anything you want,
it's on me.

27:25.852 --> 27:27.562
{\an3}Wait a second.
What's going on here?

27:27.645 --> 27:29.397
The Celts won, and I'm back
in the land of living, my man.

27:29.481 --> 27:30.565
{\an3}Oh, yeah?

27:30.648 --> 27:32.901
Nat, if I ever want
to make another bet,

27:32.984 --> 27:34.402
slap me upside the head,
would you?

27:34.486 --> 27:35.236
Okay, I will.

27:35.320 --> 27:36.863
I cannot wait
to see Jeff Stellar.

27:36.946 --> 27:39.532
How much did you bet?

27:39.616 --> 27:40.575
Fifteen.

27:40.658 --> 27:42.619
You're jumping up
and down over $15?

27:42.702 --> 27:44.037
Hundred, Steve.

27:44.120 --> 27:45.663
$1,500.

27:45.997 --> 27:48.541
(laughing):
Yeah. You're kidding.

27:48.625 --> 27:49.542
No.

27:49.626 --> 27:51.419
You got to be out of your mind.

27:51.503 --> 27:52.754
Not anymore.

27:52.837 --> 27:54.756
Brandon, I hate
to burst your bubble,

27:54.839 --> 27:55.965
but what makes you think

27:56.049 --> 27:58.593
Stellar can come up
with that kind of dough?

27:58.676 --> 27:59.677
Come on, Steve.

27:59.761 --> 28:02.430
No bookie would ever take a bet
he couldn't cover.

28:02.514 --> 28:03.890
Guys get seriously ill
from doing stuff like that.

28:03.973 --> 28:07.060
Brandon, he takes penny ante
bets from school boys.

28:07.143 --> 28:08.853
$10, $20, maybe $30.

28:08.937 --> 28:11.940
You're talking about
some real money here.

28:12.023 --> 28:12.941
{\an3}Stellar hasn't
got it.

28:13.024 --> 28:15.402
Well, he better have it.

28:15.485 --> 28:16.861
Yeah, well, he might not.

28:27.580 --> 28:28.331
Well, there he is.

28:28.415 --> 28:30.792
{\an1}Yeah, at least
he showed up at school.

28:30.875 --> 28:31.167
{\an3}That's a good
sign, isn't it?

28:31.251 --> 28:32.794
{\an3}Good luck.

28:32.877 --> 28:34.629
Morning, Jeff.

28:34.712 --> 28:37.424
{\an1}Looks like I wasn't
overconfident at all,

28:37.507 --> 28:38.466
{\an1}was I?

28:38.550 --> 28:40.176
{\an3}Nope. You weren't
too stupid, either.

28:40.260 --> 28:42.178
{\an1}I'll find that out
when you pay me.

28:42.262 --> 28:44.472
{\an3}Don't worry, Brandon.
I got you covered.

28:44.556 --> 28:47.642
{\an1}Good. I didn't want to have
to break your kneecaps.

28:47.725 --> 28:48.435
(laughs)

28:48.518 --> 28:49.978
So, you working
this afternoon?

28:50.061 --> 28:52.147
{\an3}Good.

28:52.230 --> 28:53.648
{\an3}I don't like to carry
cash around school,

28:53.731 --> 28:54.858
so, I'll see you
at the Pit later.

28:54.941 --> 28:57.152
Yeah, make it
before 6:00.

28:57.235 --> 28:58.486
No problem.

29:00.864 --> 29:02.991
So?

29:03.074 --> 29:03.950
{\an3}So it looks
like he's got it,

29:04.033 --> 29:05.869
{\an3}or he's going to
have it by tonight.

29:05.952 --> 29:08.371
{\an1}You lead a charmed
life, Brandon.

29:08.455 --> 29:10.373
Yeah.

29:18.173 --> 29:19.841
Andrea.

29:19.924 --> 29:21.384
(clears throat)

29:21.468 --> 29:22.802
Hi.

29:22.886 --> 29:24.888
Uh, Dylan, look,

29:24.971 --> 29:27.056
I'm... I'm sorry
about yesterday.

29:27.140 --> 29:29.309
No. That's, uh...
that's why I'm here, actually.

29:29.392 --> 29:31.895
I thought about what you said,
and, um,

29:31.978 --> 29:33.855
I don't know,
maybe you're right.

29:33.938 --> 29:37.484
Maybe... Maybe telling my story
will help somehow.

29:37.567 --> 29:37.984
You mean that?

29:38.067 --> 29:40.028
Yeah.

29:40.111 --> 29:42.030
I just... I don't want you
to write it.

29:42.113 --> 29:45.200
Oh, uh, what,

29:45.283 --> 29:48.203
{\an3}you want Brandon
to write it?

29:48.286 --> 29:49.037
No. I, uh...

29:49.120 --> 29:51.831
I want to write it.

29:51.915 --> 29:54.459
You do?

29:54.542 --> 29:55.835
Yeah.

29:55.919 --> 29:57.212
I can put two sentences
together, you know.

29:57.295 --> 29:58.755
I know.

29:58.838 --> 30:00.673
I... I didn't mean it like that.

30:00.757 --> 30:02.091
The thing is, I...
I don't know...

30:02.175 --> 30:04.052
I don't know
if I want it published.

30:04.135 --> 30:06.554
You know, I just want
to write it first, and...

30:06.638 --> 30:08.848
I'd like you
to help me.

30:08.932 --> 30:10.558
Sure.

30:10.642 --> 30:11.893
I'd love to.

30:11.976 --> 30:13.686
Thanks.

30:16.814 --> 30:18.066
{\an6}KELLY:
Are you ready
for this?

30:18.149 --> 30:21.778
{\an1}I gained two pounds yesterday,
and I didn't eat anything.

30:21.861 --> 30:22.904
{\an1}Something is definitely
wrong with me.

30:22.987 --> 30:25.198
{\an3}Nothing is wrong
with you.

30:25.281 --> 30:26.407
{\an3}It's probably
just water.

30:26.491 --> 30:28.201
{\an3}What time of
the month is it?

30:28.284 --> 30:29.410
No, it's not that.

30:29.494 --> 30:31.955
{\an1}I'm just on my way
to being a bona fide porker.

30:32.038 --> 30:33.206
(laughing):
What? I'm serious.

30:33.289 --> 30:35.792
{\an1}When I was little,
I was a major butterball,

30:35.875 --> 30:38.962
and no matter what anybody said,
it was definitely not cute.

30:39.045 --> 30:42.382
I'm never going to let myself
get that way again.

30:42.465 --> 30:44.592
{\an3}I'm prepared
this time.

30:44.676 --> 30:46.052
What is that?

30:46.135 --> 30:47.095
Don't worry, I bought
'em at the drugstore.

30:47.178 --> 30:49.097
They're harmless.

30:49.180 --> 30:50.181
{\an3}It's just one of those
over-the-counter diet pills.

30:50.265 --> 30:50.974
Do they work?

30:51.057 --> 30:53.476
I don't know,

30:53.560 --> 30:55.144
but if it does what the ad
says, it'll cut my appetite

30:55.228 --> 30:57.939
{\an3}and help me to lose those
stubborn five pounds.

30:58.022 --> 30:58.982
Well, I don't see five pounds.
I think you look great.

30:59.065 --> 31:01.359
That's camouflage.

31:01.442 --> 31:03.903
I'm just glad it's
not bikini season.

31:09.534 --> 31:11.619
{\an5}ANDREA:
<i>The best advice</i>
<i>anybody ever gave me</i>

31:11.703 --> 31:14.789
{\an1}about writing was: "Don't
talk about it, do it."

31:14.872 --> 31:15.915
{\an3}Ah, yes, the
Nike approach.

31:15.999 --> 31:19.919
{\an1}All I can say is, if I had
a house like this to myself,

31:20.003 --> 31:20.962
{\an1}I could write
and write and write.

31:21.045 --> 31:23.590
You sound like
Virginia Woolf.

31:23.673 --> 31:25.341
{\an1}You read
<i>A Room of One's Own?</i>

31:25.425 --> 31:26.801
{\an3}Oh, yeah.

31:26.884 --> 31:28.803
{\an1}We just read that
in AP English class.

31:28.886 --> 31:30.179
{\an3}Oh, you guys read some
great stuff in that class.

31:30.263 --> 31:32.640
Brandon showed me
your reading list.

31:32.724 --> 31:34.309
{\an1}Well, you should have
taken that class.

31:34.392 --> 31:36.603
I mean, you... you've
done most of the work.

31:36.686 --> 31:38.980
Eh, like I should have done a
lot of things, but I didn't.

31:39.063 --> 31:41.524
And why didn't you?

31:41.608 --> 31:43.151
I mean, I spent my whole life
fighting my father,

31:43.234 --> 31:47.113
and now that he's not here
to fight anymore, I kind of...

31:47.196 --> 31:48.031
I realize
he was right all along.

31:48.114 --> 31:50.325
I was just too stubborn

31:50.408 --> 31:51.826
to admit it.

31:51.909 --> 31:53.703
{\an1}It's not too late
(laughs)e.

31:53.786 --> 31:54.954
That's what he said.

31:55.038 --> 31:56.122
Well, then do it.

31:56.205 --> 31:59.000
{\an1}I mean, it's three months
until graduation.

31:59.083 --> 32:01.169
Yeah, but will three months
of hard work make up

32:01.252 --> 32:03.963
for three years of goofing off?

32:04.047 --> 32:05.632
{\an1}Well, I know, uh,
one class you can start with.

32:05.715 --> 32:07.008
AP English?

32:07.091 --> 32:09.177
{\an1}Look, you've done most
of the work.

32:09.260 --> 32:11.220
You think Meyers
He might.for it?

32:11.304 --> 32:13.556
If we talk to him.

