33:55.199 --> 33:58.911
♪ You're so precious to me ♪

33:58.995 --> 34:03.958
♪ Am I precious to you? ♪

34:04.041 --> 34:05.752
(song ends)

34:05.835 --> 34:06.961
Well, that's the final mix.

34:07.044 --> 34:09.005
Huh, what do you think?

34:09.088 --> 34:09.589
Is this terrific or what?!

34:09.672 --> 34:11.299
Yeah, yeah, I guess so.

34:11.382 --> 34:13.801
You guess so?

34:13.885 --> 34:16.219
This has platinum
written all over it.

34:16.304 --> 34:19.974
I guess it's just, uh,
still kind of hard

34:20.056 --> 34:22.018
hearing my own stuff,
that's all.

34:22.101 --> 34:24.812
Artists--
you're all so insecure.

34:24.896 --> 34:26.438
{\an1}Believe me,
this stuff is great.

34:26.522 --> 34:28.815
Yeah, we've got a meeting
with Curtis Bray tomorrow.

34:28.900 --> 34:30.193
{\an5}(laughing):
When he hears this,
he's going to flip out.

34:30.275 --> 34:32.195
Well, what if he doesn't?

34:32.277 --> 34:34.447
David...

34:34.530 --> 34:35.864
(exhales loudly)

34:35.947 --> 34:37.992
Mellow. Hmm? Hmm?

34:38.076 --> 34:39.619
He's going to love it.

34:42.789 --> 34:46.167
Brandon, why didn't you tell me
a little bit about this sooner?

34:46.250 --> 34:47.168
Maybe I could have helped.

34:47.251 --> 34:49.337
I didn't want anyone to know.

34:49.420 --> 34:51.880
{\an3}You could always go
to your dad.

34:51.964 --> 34:53.174
No, no, I can't
tell my dad.

34:53.257 --> 34:54.342
I've been lying to him
for too long,

34:54.425 --> 34:56.761
telling him I'm just
betting chump change.

34:56.844 --> 34:57.929
It's not his problem. I can't
drag him into it.

34:58.012 --> 35:00.640
{\an3}Yeah, well, which is worse,
telling your dad or Duke?

35:00.723 --> 35:02.350
I don't know.

35:02.433 --> 35:04.227
I'm out of control, man--
I don't know what

35:04.310 --> 35:06.395
I would have done to that kid
if you wouldn't have shown up.

35:06.479 --> 35:10.191
{\an6}How could you even expect
Jeff to come up with that
kind of money?

35:10.274 --> 35:12.902
I don't know.

35:12.985 --> 35:14.153
Maybe you could go to your mom.

35:14.237 --> 35:15.321
Tell her some kind of sob story.

35:15.404 --> 35:17.198
No, I don't think so.

35:17.281 --> 35:19.200
She put the brakes on that kind
of thing a long time ago.

35:19.283 --> 35:20.535
{\an3}She gives me a check at the
beginning of the month

35:20.618 --> 35:21.994
and I've got to make it last.

35:22.078 --> 35:23.704
{\an3}And it's all gone right
now, except $300.

35:23.788 --> 35:24.747
I'll take it.

35:24.831 --> 35:25.748
Yeah, but then what?

35:25.832 --> 35:27.166
Then I'll pray.

35:27.250 --> 35:29.710
What do you think
they're gonna do to me,

35:29.794 --> 35:31.212
break my nose,
maybe break my thumbs?

35:31.295 --> 35:33.714
No. Not for $1,500.

35:33.798 --> 35:36.217
Steve, he's got this big goon
that drives him around.

35:36.300 --> 35:39.011
They're just trying
to scare you; you'll see.

35:39.095 --> 35:40.096
I don't think so.

35:58.823 --> 35:59.574
Hey, BrandHi.

35:59.657 --> 36:02.743
I got soHow much?for you.

36:02.827 --> 36:04.036
200 bucks, that's it?

36:04.120 --> 36:05.163
Don't sweat it, Brandon.

36:05.246 --> 36:06.581
{\an1}There'll be more
in a couple of days.

36:06.664 --> 36:07.915
{\an1}But you better keep
your hands off me

36:07.999 --> 36:08.749
{\an1}or you can forget
about seeing a penny.

36:08.833 --> 36:11.043
{\an3}Look, Jeff, don't
worry about it.

36:11.127 --> 36:12.336
{\an6}You're not the one
who's gonna take the
heat around here, I am.

36:14.422 --> 36:15.548
{\an1}I know it's almost
the end of the year,

36:15.631 --> 36:16.757
{\an1}but he's read most
of the books.

36:16.841 --> 36:17.675
{\an1}He's smarter than
half the class.

36:17.758 --> 36:19.886
{\an3}Why this sudden
interest in literature?

36:19.969 --> 36:21.596
{\an1}'Cause he wants
to turn his life around.

36:21.679 --> 36:23.764
This is the first step.

36:23.848 --> 36:25.391
Where is he?

36:25.474 --> 36:28.269
Outside.

36:33.399 --> 36:36.777
{\an1}I hear you want
to be in my class.

36:36.861 --> 36:38.738
If you'll have me.

36:38.821 --> 36:40.489
{\an1}I'll talk to Mrs. Teasley
about it.

36:40.573 --> 36:42.491
{\an1}But first, there are
a few conditions.

36:42.575 --> 36:43.576
{\an3}Like...?

36:43.659 --> 36:45.578
You can't cut.

36:45.661 --> 36:46.954
Okay.

36:47.038 --> 36:47.413
And you'll do the work.

36:47.496 --> 36:49.290
I can do that.

36:49.373 --> 36:50.666
And you'll think.

36:50.750 --> 36:52.668
That might be a tough one.

36:52.752 --> 36:55.504
Somehow I doubt that.

36:56.589 --> 36:59.383
(phone ringing)

37:01.385 --> 37:03.179
{\an3}Brandon...

37:03.262 --> 37:05.139
Nat's on the phone for you.

37:05.222 --> 37:06.515
Did you tell him I was here?

37:06.599 --> 37:08.643
Well, of course I did.

37:10.728 --> 37:12.813
Thanks.

37:15.066 --> 37:16.275
Hey, Nat.

37:16.359 --> 37:18.611
Brando, you better
get in here.

37:18.694 --> 37:19.320
Duke's waiting for you.

37:19.403 --> 37:22.114
And he's not happy.

37:23.199 --> 37:24.867
God, Nat, do me a favor.

37:24.951 --> 37:26.494
Don't tell him where
I live, okay?

37:26.577 --> 37:28.996
Believe me, pal,
he already knows.

37:31.707 --> 37:32.583
Thanks.

37:37.630 --> 37:41.425
(pop music playing)

37:45.554 --> 37:47.431
(music ends)

37:51.268 --> 37:54.689
So David, what
do you think, hmm?

37:54.772 --> 37:57.316
I have to say, it's the best
work I've ever done.

37:57.400 --> 37:58.526
Really?

37:58.609 --> 37:59.485
Oh, absolutely.

37:59.568 --> 38:00.653
I love the way
the song turned out.

38:00.736 --> 38:04.532
You know, in my career,

38:04.615 --> 38:07.702
I've always prided myself on
being able to spot talent.

38:07.785 --> 38:08.369
It's a gift I have.

38:08.452 --> 38:11.205
Absolutely. A gift.

38:11.288 --> 38:15.543
{\an3}But every now and then,
my vision clouds.

38:15.626 --> 38:17.712
Who knows why?

38:17.795 --> 38:20.548
{\an1}I mean, you can't
explain these things.

38:22.675 --> 38:24.885
{\an1}The sound isn't what
I was hoping for.

38:24.969 --> 38:26.470
{\an3}Yeah, I think I know
what you mean.

38:27.638 --> 38:29.432
In fact, I didn't want
to bring this up,

38:29.515 --> 38:31.392
but when you asked me
to produce this album,

38:31.475 --> 38:35.229
this wasn't at all
what I thought

38:35.312 --> 38:36.355
I'd have to work with.

38:36.439 --> 38:38.566
Wait a second,
I don't understand.

38:38.649 --> 38:39.734
You said that

38:39.817 --> 38:44.363
that was my best material.
The most commercial song I had.

38:44.447 --> 38:46.198
I keep trying to tell the kid

38:46.282 --> 38:47.241
it all comes down
to the material.

38:47.324 --> 38:49.535
If it isn't there, no matter
how much production

38:49.618 --> 38:52.288
{\an3}you throw at it,
it won't work.

38:52.371 --> 38:55.541
So true, Serge, so true.

38:55.624 --> 38:58.878
The producer serves
the material,

38:58.961 --> 38:59.754
the artist guides the product.

38:59.837 --> 39:02.965
That's what I was
trying to explain.

39:03.049 --> 39:03.924
But you chose the song.

39:04.008 --> 39:05.384
I didn't even want to use it.

39:05.468 --> 39:05.926
I wanted to go with
the hip-hop stuff.

39:06.010 --> 39:07.762
You didn't say anything.

39:07.845 --> 39:08.888
Serge is a producer,

39:08.971 --> 39:10.931
not a mind reader, David.

39:11.015 --> 39:13.559
Well, I can do other material.

39:13.642 --> 39:15.603
Sorry, kid, it's just not
going to work out.

39:15.686 --> 39:17.480
So that's it?

39:17.563 --> 39:18.939
I don't even get another chance?

39:19.023 --> 39:20.566
You're young, kid.

39:20.649 --> 39:22.610
{\an1}There'll be plenty
more chances for you.

39:22.693 --> 39:25.404
But it wasn't my fault.

39:25.488 --> 39:25.946
You heard my songs.

39:26.030 --> 39:27.948
David, I heard a demo.

39:28.032 --> 39:29.617
{\an1}A teenager fooling around
in his garage.

39:29.700 --> 39:32.661
Do you know how many more
teenagers there are out there?

39:32.745 --> 39:34.580
{\an1}Hmm?

39:34.663 --> 39:36.040
Good luck.

39:38.542 --> 39:41.462
David.

39:41.545 --> 39:45.299
{\an1}Well, kid, we tried.
It's showbiz.

39:45.382 --> 39:46.092
{\an3}No it isn't. This has nothing
to do with show business.

39:46.175 --> 39:48.135
{\an3}You're just an
over-the-hill hack

39:48.219 --> 39:50.930
{\an6}with no taste trying to
hold on to a lousy job,
and you know what?

39:51.013 --> 39:53.974
I don't need you
or Icon Records.

39:55.601 --> 39:59.688
{\an1}Dylan, how long are you
going to do be doing that?

39:59.772 --> 40:01.649
{\an3}Kel, I told you-- I'm writing,
and it's not something

40:01.732 --> 40:04.276
{\an3}I know when
I'm going to finish.

40:04.360 --> 40:05.820
{\an3}Can't you do homework
or something?

40:05.903 --> 40:07.947
I guess.

40:11.742 --> 40:15.788
{\an1}But I can think of something
I'd rather be doing.

40:15.871 --> 40:18.290
Can you?

40:18.374 --> 40:21.794
Not now Kel, come on.

40:21.877 --> 40:23.671
{\an3}Well, at least I can read
what you've written.

40:23.754 --> 40:27.716
No, not until it's finished.

40:27.800 --> 40:29.718
Great.

40:29.802 --> 40:32.847
{\an3}Hey, it's not
personal, okay?

40:32.930 --> 40:35.516
{\an3}It's just, I'm writing
about my dad

40:35.599 --> 40:36.517
{\an3}and feelings and
stuff and...

40:36.600 --> 40:40.354
{\an3}I just don't want to
share it until it's done.

40:40.437 --> 40:40.729
I understand.

40:40.813 --> 40:41.689
You sure?

40:41.772 --> 40:44.567
Yeah.

40:44.650 --> 40:45.568
I told Donna and David
that I'd meet them

40:45.651 --> 40:46.569
at the Peach Pit anyway.

40:46.652 --> 40:49.363
All right.
I'll call you later.

40:49.446 --> 40:50.990
You don't have to.

40:51.073 --> 40:52.199
I want to.

40:53.492 --> 40:54.410
Don't be mad.

40:54.493 --> 40:56.912
I'll be fine.

40:56.996 --> 40:58.706
{\an1}Just go on back
to your writing, okay?

41:07.631 --> 41:08.966
(sighs)

41:24.481 --> 41:25.441
{\an3}Hi, Duke.

41:25.524 --> 41:26.483
{\an1}Brandon.

41:26.567 --> 41:28.319
And how are you today?

41:30.070 --> 41:32.406
Ah, okay... one,

41:32.489 --> 41:33.407
two,

41:33.490 --> 41:35.409
three, four,

41:35.492 --> 41:37.244
five...

41:37.328 --> 41:38.621
Five.

41:38.704 --> 41:40.623
{\an1}What, are you
kidding me or what?

41:40.706 --> 41:43.083
Huh? You owe me three times
this much.

41:43.167 --> 41:44.585
I know.

41:44.668 --> 41:45.252
The rest is coming.

41:45.336 --> 41:46.879
I just need a little more time.

41:46.962 --> 41:48.380
{\an1}You never learn,
do you kid?

41:48.464 --> 41:49.798
It's a good thing you got
such good friends.

41:54.803 --> 41:57.598
{\an1}And you owe your
good friend Nathaniel here

41:57.681 --> 42:00.976
a thousand bucks, huh?

42:01.060 --> 42:02.728
Nice to see you, Nat.

42:02.811 --> 42:06.357
Lay low for awhile, kid.

42:14.573 --> 42:16.242
You paid off Duke for me?

42:16.325 --> 42:17.660
Yeah.

42:17.743 --> 42:18.786
{\an3}And you're gonna work
off every cent.

42:18.869 --> 42:20.829
I will, Nat, I promise,
Every last cent.

42:20.913 --> 42:25.084
How many times did I ask you:
Is everything all right?

42:25.167 --> 42:26.252
Could you handle this?

42:26.335 --> 42:26.877
You were right.

42:26.961 --> 42:28.837
(sighs)

42:28.921 --> 42:30.673
I got out of control.

42:33.175 --> 42:35.261
Nah, it's more than that.

42:35.344 --> 42:36.637
{\an3}You know how many
gamblers think

42:36.720 --> 42:37.805
{\an3}they can get out
of the hole

42:37.888 --> 42:39.640
by betting again and again
and again?

42:39.723 --> 42:41.684
I know.

42:41.767 --> 42:42.768
Do you?

42:46.105 --> 42:49.149
I ever catch you
gambling again,

42:49.233 --> 42:51.652
the first call I make
is to your father.

42:51.735 --> 42:54.655
Thanks, Nat.

42:54.738 --> 42:58.659
I won't forget this.

42:58.742 --> 43:00.619
Neither will I.

43:07.126 --> 43:07.668
So, how'd it go?

43:07.751 --> 43:10.671
Down the tubes.

43:10.754 --> 43:11.505
What?

43:11.588 --> 43:13.465
They dumped me.

43:13.549 --> 43:15.009
Why?

43:15.092 --> 43:16.593
'Cause Bray hated the song.

43:18.596 --> 43:20.180
We all hated the song.

43:20.264 --> 43:21.098
At least he showed
he had taste.

43:21.181 --> 43:22.891
{\an3}So that's it, the
whole thing's over?

43:22.975 --> 43:27.521
{\an6}Well, it's better to be
dumped than have your name
on something that you hate.

43:27.605 --> 43:28.063
Yeah, I guess so.

43:28.147 --> 43:29.857
(hip-hop music playing)

43:29.940 --> 43:34.528
Hmm, now that's a song.

43:34.611 --> 43:37.448
Maybe next time,
you'll listen to me.

43:37.531 --> 43:41.201
Does that mean there
might be a next time?

43:41.285 --> 43:44.663
{\an3}There might be.
If you listen to me.

43:44.747 --> 43:46.665
So, who wants what?

43:46.749 --> 43:47.833
{\an3}I think we'll all
have hamburgers

43:47.916 --> 43:49.668
{\an1}and French fries,
on me.

43:49.752 --> 43:51.712
Ah! What's the occasion?

43:51.795 --> 43:54.131
Silver and I are
back in business.

43:56.759 --> 43:58.177
{\an1}You know, I'm not very hungry.
I'll just have coffee.

43:58.260 --> 43:59.636
Okay, doll.

44:01.555 --> 44:03.724
Look, don't you think

44:03.807 --> 44:05.059
you're overdoing this diet
thing a little bit?

44:05.142 --> 44:07.853
Donna, I've already lost
a pound and a half.

44:07.936 --> 44:09.605
Only have a few more to go.

44:09.688 --> 44:10.439
Stop worrying about me.

44:10.522 --> 44:11.940
I'll be right back, okay?

44:15.694 --> 44:16.737
So, what do you think?

44:16.820 --> 44:17.738
This is a good song.

44:19.531 --> 44:21.116
(sighs)
